What you need to know:

There is no doubt that Badi has started well.How he transforms Nairobi will also be Uhuru Kenyatta’s legacy after he snatched it from the hands of Governor Gideon Mbuvi Sonko.When Ainsworth arrived, Nairobi “had neither body to be kicked nor soul to be damned; it has neither taxes nor rates nor restrictions,” one observer wrote.More than 120 years later, Nairobi is facing the same problems that Ainsworth encountered.